cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on investigating the effect of various dependency-based word embeddings on distinguishing between functional and domain similarity, word similarity rankings, and two downstream tasks in English. These tasks are related to natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as linear regression and neural networks, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the embeddings on several datasets, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
